# Adding a New Filament Profile

When the user asks to add a new filament, follow this complete workflow.

## 1. Gather Info

- Ask for the **Amazon product URL**, **official product page**, and/or **TDS PDF link**
- Download the **TDS PDF** and save it in the filament's brand folder as `<Brand>_<Material>_TDS.pdf`
- Printer is **Bambu Lab H2S**
- Nozzle sizes: **0.2, 0.4, 0.6, 0.8mm** (both Standard and High Flow)
- Profile names do NOT use a `my-` prefix

## 2. Create Filament Brand/Material Folder

Create `c:\GitHub\filments settings\<Brand>\<Material>\` (e.g., `SUNLU\PETG-HS\`, `Inslogic\ASA\`)

### Required contents:
- **TDS PDF**: Downloaded from manufacturer (e.g., `SUNLU_PETG_HS_TDS.pdf`)
- **Base filament profiles**: 4 JSON files (one per nozzle size)
- **Process presets**: 4 JSON + 4 .info files (one per nozzle size) — stored alongside filament profiles
- **Calibrated override**: 1 JSON file
- **README.md** containing:
  - Product info (brand, material, diameter)
  - Links: Amazon product page, official manufacturer page, TDS PDF download link
  - Full TDS material properties table (mechanical: tensile, flexural, impact, elongation; thermal: HDT, Tg, Vicat, melting temp; other: density, shrinkage)
  - Manufacturer recommended print settings from TDS
  - Table of all created profile files with key settings per nozzle

## 3. Create Filament Base Profiles

Location: `filament/base/` in BambuStudio path
`C:\Users\Nir\AppData\Roaming\BambuStudio\user\2189385007\filament\base\`

Create **4 JSON files** (one per nozzle):
- `<Brand> <Material> @Bambu Lab H2S 0.2 nozzle.json`
- `<Brand> <Material> @Bambu Lab H2S 0.4 nozzle.json`
- `<Brand> <Material> @Bambu Lab H2S 0.6 nozzle.json`
- `<Brand> <Material> @Bambu Lab H2S 0.8 nozzle.json`

Each JSON must have:
- **All 145 fields** matching working Bambu Studio profiles (compare with existing profiles)
- `"version": "2.6.0.2"` (match current Bambu Studio version)
- `"from": "User"`
- `"filament_extruder_variant": ["Direct Drive Standard", "Direct Drive High Flow"]`
- `"compatible_printers": ["Bambu Lab H2S X.X nozzle"]`
- `"filament_id"`: format `P` + 7 hex chars (same ID across all nozzle sizes for same filament)
- Dual-value arrays `[standard_value, high_flow_value]` for speed/temp/retraction fields

### TDS-Critical Fields to verify against manufacturer specs:
- `filament_density` — must match TDS density value
- `temperature_vitrification` — must match TDS Tg value
- `filament_dev_ams_drying_heat_distortion_temperature` — must match TDS HDT value
- `filament_dev_drying_softening_temperature` — must match TDS Vicat softening value
- `hot_plate_temp` / `textured_plate_temp` / `eng_plate_temp` — must be within TDS bed temp range
- `nozzle_temperature` — must be within TDS nozzle temp range
- `filament_retraction_length` — must be within TDS retraction distance range (usually 0.8-1.2mm)
- `filament_retraction_speed` / `filament_deretraction_speed` — must match TDS retraction speed

### Mandatory Validation Against Bambu System Profiles:
Always compare new profiles against the corresponding **Bambu system profile** for the same material type on H2S. System profiles are at:
`C:\Users\Nir\AppData\Roaming\BambuStudio\system\BBL\filament\`

Key fields to cross-check with Bambu system profile (these caused real issues when wrong):
- `nozzle_temperature` / `nozzle_temperature_initial_layer` — match Bambu's values, NOT TDS low-end
- `hot_plate_temp` / `eng_plate_temp` / `textured_plate_temp` — match Bambu's values (often higher than TDS minimum)
- `fan_max_speed` / `fan_min_speed` — **MUST match Bambu's values** (too high = stringing on PETG, no extrusion on ASA)
- `overhang_fan_speed` — match Bambu (typically 50% for PETG, 80-100% for ASA)
- `enable_pressure_advance` — must be `"1"` (enabled), never `"0"`
- `filament_retraction_speed` — must NOT be `"nil"` for any extruder
- `filament_deretraction_speed` — must NOT be `"nil"`, should match retraction speed
- `filament_start_gcode` — must include aux fan control gcode (copy from Bambu system profile for same material type)

### Material-specific Fan Speed Reference (from Bambu system profiles):
| Material | fan_max_speed | fan_min_speed | overhang_fan_speed |
|----------|--------------|--------------|-------------------|
| PETG | 60% | 20% | 50% |
| ASA | 35% | 10% | 80-100% |
| PLA | 100% | 100% | 90% |
| PA/Nylon | 30% | 10% | 50% |
| TPU | 100% | 100% | 100% |

### Filament Start Gcode (copy from Bambu system profile for material type):
PETG/PLA use:
```
; filament start gcode\n{if (bed_temperature[current_extruder] >80)||(bed_temperature_initial_layer[current_extruder] >80)}M106 P3 S255\n{elsif (bed_temperature[current_extruder] >60)||(bed_temperature_initial_layer[current_extruder] >60)}M106 P3 S180\n{endif}\n\n{if activate_air_filtration[current_extruder] && support_air_filtration}\nM106 P3 S{during_print_exhaust_fan_speed_num[current_extruder]} \n{endif}
```

Each JSON needs a matching `.info` file:
```
sync_info = 
user_id = 
setting_id = PFUS<12 random hex chars>
base_id = 
updated_time = <unix timestamp>
```
- No BOM encoding, use ASCII, Unix line endings (`\n`)
- Each `.info` must have a unique `setting_id`

## 4. Create Filament User Presets

Location: `filament/` in BambuStudio path
`C:\Users\Nir\AppData\Roaming\BambuStudio\user\2189385007\filament\`

Create **4 user preset JSON files** (one per nozzle) + **1 Calibrated override**:

User preset format (sparse, inherits from base):
```json
{
    "filament_extruder_variant": ["Direct Drive Standard", "Direct Drive High Flow"],
    "filament_flow_ratio": ["nil", "nil"],
    "filament_settings_id": ["<name> @Bambu Lab H2S 0.4 nozzle"],
    "from": "User",
    "inherits": "<name> @Bambu Lab H2S 0.4 nozzle",
    "name": "<name> @Bambu Lab H2S 0.4 nozzle",
    "version": "2.6.0.2"
}
```

Each needs a matching `.info` file:
```
sync_info = 
user_id = 2189385007
setting_id = PFUS<12 random hex>
base_id = <setting_id from matching base .info>
updated_time = <unix timestamp>
```

## 5. Create Process Presets

Location: `process/` in BambuStudio path
`C:\Users\Nir\AppData\Roaming\BambuStudio\user\2189385007\process\`

Create **4 process preset JSON files** (one per nozzle), inheriting from system profiles:

| Nozzle | Inherits From | Layer Height | base_id |
|--------|--------------|-------------|---------|
| 0.2mm | `0.10mm Standard @BBL H2S 0.2 nozzle` | 0.10mm | GP152 |
| 0.4mm | `0.20mm Standard @BBL H2S` | 0.20mm | GP158 |
| 0.6mm | `0.30mm Standard @BBL H2S 0.6 nozzle` | 0.30mm | GP159 |
| 0.8mm | `0.40mm Standard @BBL H2S 0.8 nozzle` | 0.40mm | GP156 |

Naming: `<Brand> <Material> <layer>mm @H2S <nozzle> nozzle`

Default settings to include:
- `sparse_infill_pattern`: `gyroid`
- `sparse_infill_density`: `20%`
- `wall_loops`: `4`
- `enable_support`: `1`
- `support_top_z_distance`: match Bambu system default (0.2mm for 0.4/0.6/0.8 nozzle, 0.1mm for 0.2 nozzle)
- `brim_type`: `outer_and_inner` for ASA (bed adhesion critical without glue)
- `initial_layer_speed`: 30-35mm/s for ASA (slower = better adhesion)
- Speed overrides appropriate for the filament material and TDS max speed

Process preset files are stored in the brand/material folder (e.g., `Inslogic\ASA\`) alongside filament profiles, NOT in a separate `process\` folder.

Process `.info` files use `PPUS` prefix (not `PFUS`):
```
sync_info = 
user_id = 2189385007
setting_id = PPUS<12 random hex>
base_id = <system GP ID from table above>
updated_time = <unix timestamp>
```

## 6. Update DeployPack

Copy all new files to `c:\GitHub\filments settings\DeployPack\` as a **flat folder** (no subdirectories):
- Base filament profiles (.json + .info)
- Calibrated override (.json + .info)
- Process presets (.json + .info)
- `deploy.ps1` script handles copying to correct BambuStudio subdirectories

### Current DeployPack contents (this repo)

- **SUNLU PETG HS only:** 4 base + 4 base `.info` + 4 user `.preset` pairs + 1 Calibrated pair + 4 process pairs = **26** profile files (`.json` / `.info`), plus `deploy.ps1`.
- Regenerate from repo root: `python3 SUNLU/PETG-HS/gen_sunlu_petg_hs.py` (writes `SUNLU/PETG-HS/` and `DeployPack/`).

