## 12. Lessons Learned (Common Profile Mistakes)

These are real issues encountered during profile creation and tuning:

### PETG Stringing
- **Root cause:** Fan speeds too high (80-90% max, 40-50% min) vs Bambu's 60%/20%
- **Fix:** Match Bambu PETG fan speeds (max 60%, min 20%, overhang 50%)
- Over-cooling PETG causes outer shell to freeze while core stays molten — retraction pulls the molten core through the hardened shell creating strings
- Also lowered nozzle temps 5°C below TDS range to further reduce stringing

### ASA Not Extruding / Calibration Failure
- **Root cause 1:** `fan_max_speed` at 100% (Bambu uses 35%) — solidified filament at nozzle tip
- **Root cause 2:** `nozzle_temperature` at 255-260°C (Bambu uses 270°C for ALL nozzle sizes on H2S)
- **Root cause 3:** `enable_pressure_advance` was `"0"` (disabled)
- **Root cause 4:** `filament_retraction_speed` and `filament_deretraction_speed` set to `"nil"` for Standard extruder
- **Root cause 5:** Bed temps 10°C too low (90°C vs Bambu's 100°C)
- **Fix:** Match all values to Bambu ASA system profile, enable pressure advance, set explicit retraction/deretraction speeds

### ASA Support Disconnecting from Plate
- **Root cause:** `support_top_z_distance` was 0.3mm (too large — support ends too far from part)
- **Fix:** Reduced to 0.2mm (0.4/0.6/0.8 nozzle) and 0.1mm (0.2 nozzle) to match Bambu system defaults
- Rule of thumb: support-to-part gap should be roughly equal to 1 layer height
- Also added `brim_type: outer_and_inner` (5mm) to all ASA process presets for better bed adhesion
- Set `initial_layer_speed` to 30-35mm/s (slower first layer = better adhesion for ASA)

### Matte PLA Nozzle Temp Too Low
- **Root cause:** Standard extruder temps for 0.2mm and 0.4mm nozzles were below 220°C (matching TDS low-end), but Bambu PLA system profile uses 220°C minimum
- **Fix:** Raised Standard extruder nozzle temp to minimum 220°C for 0.2mm and 0.4mm nozzles

### Silk PLA Nozzle Temp Inconsistency
- **Root cause:** Different temps per nozzle size (215-225°C) — Silk PLA needs consistent higher temp for proper flow and silk finish
- **Fix:** Unified all nozzle sizes to 230/230°C (STD/HF) for consistent silk particle orientation

### General Rules
- NEVER set `filament_retraction_speed` or `filament_deretraction_speed` to `"nil"` — always use explicit values (35mm/s is a safe default)
- NEVER set `enable_pressure_advance` to `"0"` — always enable it
- NEVER trust TDS fan speed recommendations blindly — always compare with Bambu system profile for the same material
- `nozzle_temperature_initial_layer` should be >= `nozzle_temperature` (calibration uses initial layer temp)
- Always include proper `filament_start_gcode` with aux fan control from Bambu system profiles
- `support_top_z_distance` should match Bambu system defaults (0.2mm for standard nozzles, 0.1mm for 0.2 nozzle) — NOT arbitrary values

### Recommended Build Plate per Material
| Material | Best Plate | Glue? | Notes |
|----------|-----------|-------|-------|
| PETG | Textured PEI | No | Good adhesion + easy release. Never use smooth PEI (bonds permanently) |
| ASA | Engineering plate | Yes (recommended) | Textured PEI too slippery for supports |
| PA/Nylon | Textured PEI | Yes (required) | Nylon always needs glue |
| PLA (all) | Any plate | No | Avoid engineering plate (bonds too hard) |
| TPU | Textured PEI | No | Good adhesion + easy release. Low bed temp (35°C) |
